--- CompleteMazeBuilder Position Fixes & Outer Walls - 2026-03-04
+++ Assets/Scripts/Core/06_Maze/CompleteMazeBuilder.cs

ISSUE:
======
Incorrect positions throughout CompleteMazeBuilder.cs causing:
- Walls not aligned properly
- Maze not fully enclosed (gaps in outer perimeter)
- Doors at wrong height
- Rooms misaligned
- Player spawn at wrong position

FIXES APPLIED:
==============

1. GROUND FLOOR POSITION
   BEFORE: (mazeWidth*cellSize/2 - cellSize/2, -0.1, mazeHeight*cellSize/2 - cellSize/2)
   AFTER:  (mazeWidth*cellSize/2f, -0.1, mazeHeight*cellSize/2f)
   → Properly centered

2. CEILING POSITION
   BEFORE: (mazeWidth*cellSize/2 - cellSize/2, ceilingHeight, mazeHeight*cellSize/2 - cellSize/2)
   AFTER:  (mazeWidth*cellSize/2f, ceilingHeight, mazeHeight*cellSize/2f)
   → Properly centered

3. WALL POSITIONS
   - Fixed cell center calculation: (x*cellSize + cellSize/2f, wallHeight/2f, y*cellSize + cellSize/2f)
   - Wall segments positioned at cell boundaries correctly
   - Wall height centered: y = wallHeight/2f (was 0)
   
4. OUTER PERIMETER WALLS (NEW!)
   Added 4 loops to create boundary walls:
   - North boundary: Z = height * cellSize
   - South boundary: Z = 0
   - East boundary: X = width * cellSize
   - West boundary: X = 0
   → Maze is now FULLY ENCLOSED

5. DOOR POSITIONS
   BEFORE: cellPos +/- cellSize/2 (from wrong cellPos)
   AFTER:  Proper boundary positions:
   - East door:  ((x+1)*cellSize, wallHeight/2f, y*cellSize + cellSize/2f)
   - South door: (x*cellSize + cellSize/2f, wallHeight/2f, y*cellSize)
   → Doors centered vertically on walls

6. ROOM POSITIONS
   BEFORE: (position.x * cellSize, 0, position.y * cellSize)
   AFTER:  (position.x*cellSize + cellSize*1.5f, 0, position.y*cellSize + cellSize*1.5f)
   → Centered in 3x3 cell area

7. PLAYER SPAWN POSITION
   BEFORE: (entrancePos.x * cellSize, 1, entrancePos.y * cellSize) + offset
   AFTER:  (entrancePos.x*cellSize + cellSize*1.5f, 1, entrancePos.y*cellSize + cellSize*1.5f) + offset
   → Centered in entrance room

